	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=129533><span id=Scholar>HoraceHighwater</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>15 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.50]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>I will play an Erudite Enchanter..<br>A friend of mine who is not an Enchanter said that his Enchanter friend recommended putting some points into Stamina since &quot;it keeps chanters alive.&quot; they are both level 60s, but I can't mention names. Sorry. He said to put all points into STA but I don't feel compfortable in doing so. I was going to go 127 int 100 cha, but 122 int 95 cha and add the other 10 to STA would also be good.<br>Is there any validation in his claim? He said the +int +cha equipment is easier to get than +STA for caster. I don't know.<br>My last Enchanter (Before I quit because I was disgusted due to the growing moron population in Erollisi Marr) had 142 int 85 cha.. He was good at mezzing.. Charms rate was decent. Not exceedingly good. Could have been better. I NEVER got below 1 bubble on mana from levels 20-29 (Before Breeze). I soloed some too using the Enchanter pet--believe it or not.. it can be done. so at 142 Mana is no problem</p>&nbsp;<br>Nrim<br>Bertoxxulous' Dark Priest<br>Firona Vie</td></tr>
